00:28:50.789 --> 00:28:55.753 line:90% position:50% align:center
Brother Janne Kauppinen
is going to read a letter from the class.

00:29:01.592 --> 00:29:05.555 line:90% position:50% align:center
“To the Governing Body:

00:29:05.555 --> 00:29:08.182 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Dear brothers,

00:29:08.182 --> 00:29:12.020 line:90% position:50% align:center
“at the end of five memorable months,

00:29:12.020 --> 00:29:14.355 line:90% position:50% align:center
“we feel moved to echo

00:29:14.355 --> 00:29:17.942 line:90% position:50% align:center
“the words of 1 John 4:16:

00:29:17.942 --> 00:29:22.822 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘We have come to know and believe
the love that God has for us.’

00:29:23.531 --> 00:29:27.952 line:90% position:50% align:center
“One way we experienced this love
was by your fine example

00:29:27.952 --> 00:29:30.872 line:90% position:50% align:center
“as well as that of your helpers.

00:29:30.872 --> 00:29:33.667 line:90% position:50% align:center
“We did not expect and will never forget

00:29:33.667 --> 00:29:37.129 line:90% position:50% align:center
“you sacrificing
your precious time and energy

00:29:37.129 --> 00:29:41.758 line:90% position:50% align:center
“to provide us lectures,
interviews, and even tours.

00:29:41.758 --> 00:29:44.803 line:90% position:50% align:center
“As a result,
we learned firsthand

00:29:44.803 --> 00:29:49.558 line:90% position:50% align:center
“from your love, humility,
and burning zeal for Jehovah.

00:29:51.351 --> 00:29:54.646 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Our course of intensive Bible study

00:29:54.646 --> 00:29:56.732 line:90% position:50% align:center
“has deepened our appreciation

00:29:56.732 --> 00:29:59.902 line:90% position:50% align:center
“for the timely and upbuilding spiritual food

00:29:59.902 --> 00:30:02.446 line:90% position:50% align:center
“available to all of God’s people.

00:30:03.280 --> 00:30:05.866 line:90% position:50% align:center
“We are also deeply grateful to you

00:30:05.866 --> 00:30:10.538 line:90% position:50% align:center
“for providing us
with selfless and skillful instructors.

00:30:10.538 --> 00:30:15.334 line:90% position:50% align:center
“These ‘gifts in men’
imparted their souls to us each day

00:30:15.334 --> 00:30:19.630 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and regularly made our hearts burn
with appreciation.

00:30:22.425 --> 00:30:26.888 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Carefully considering
the entire Bible chronologically

00:30:26.888 --> 00:30:31.059 line:90% position:50% align:center
“has given us a deeper understanding
of how Jehovah thinks.

00:30:31.059 --> 00:30:36.064 line:90% position:50% align:center
“It has also increased
our sensitivity to how he feels.

00:30:37.273 --> 00:30:40.610 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Our in-depth consideration
of Jesus’ ministry

00:30:40.610 --> 00:30:45.490 line:90% position:50% align:center
“made us eyewitnesses to God’s love
being revealed through him.

00:30:46.658 --> 00:30:50.453 line:90% position:50% align:center
“We learned
that the opposite of love is selfishness.

00:30:50.453 --> 00:30:54.332 line:90% position:50% align:center
“We can only show
genuine, unselfish concern for others

00:30:54.332 --> 00:30:56.877 line:90% position:50% align:center
“with the help of holy spirit.

00:30:56.877 --> 00:30:59.379 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Such selfless love empowers us

00:30:59.379 --> 00:31:03.675 line:90% position:50% align:center
“to bring out the best
in ourselves and others.

00:31:03.675 --> 00:31:06.970 line:90% position:50% align:center
“We experienced this in action

00:31:06.970 --> 00:31:10.057 line:90% position:50% align:center
“through the warm hospitality
and overwhelming kindness

00:31:10.057 --> 00:31:12.976 line:90% position:50% align:center
“shown by the United States Bethel family,

00:31:12.976 --> 00:31:15.729 line:90% position:50% align:center
“who ‘abound in love for one another’

00:31:15.729 --> 00:31:17.815 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and for all.

00:31:17.815 --> 00:31:22.820 line:90% position:50% align:center
“This beautiful family
has a permanent place in each of our hearts.

00:31:26.407 --> 00:31:30.911 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Thank you for the priceless gift
of Gilead training.

00:31:32.830 --> 00:31:35.875 line:90% position:50% align:center
“As we leave Patterson,
we are resolved to live

00:31:35.875 --> 00:31:39.128 line:90% position:50% align:center
“by the words of 1 John 4:11:

00:31:39.128 --> 00:31:41.589 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘If this is how God loved us,

00:31:41.589 --> 00:31:45.927 line:90% position:50% align:center
“then we are also under obligation
to love one another.’

00:31:48.012 --> 00:31:53.017 line:90% position:50% align:center
“We are determined to never forget
what we saw and heard.

00:31:57.272 --> 00:31:59.774 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Gilead
—excuse me—

00:31:59.774 --> 00:32:03.445 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Gilead has changed our desire and ability

00:32:03.445 --> 00:32:07.783 line:90% position:50% align:center
“to serve Jehovah
and our brothers better each day,

00:32:07.783 --> 00:32:09.951 line:90% position:50% align:center
“stabilizing Jehovah’s organization

00:32:09.951 --> 00:32:12.954 line:90% position:50% align:center
“one precious sheep at a time.

00:32:12.954 --> 00:32:15.958 line:90% position:50% align:center
“We love you, dear brothers.

00:32:18.544 --> 00:32:23.507 line:90% position:50% align:center
Your brothers and sisters,
153rd Gilead Class.”

00:32:35.394 --> 00:32:37.980 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, at the outset of our program,

00:32:37.980 --> 00:32:41.859 line:90% position:50% align:center
we discussed the initial reluctance

00:32:41.859 --> 00:32:45.029 line:90% position:50% align:center
of Gideon and Moses

00:32:45.029 --> 00:32:48.533 line:90% position:50% align:center
and Jeremiah and Brother Booth

00:32:48.533 --> 00:32:51.452 line:90% position:50% align:center
to accept assignments.

00:32:51.452 --> 00:32:55.581 line:90% position:50% align:center
But in the final analysis,
they all followed through

00:32:55.581 --> 00:32:59.210 line:90% position:50% align:center
and they did
what Jehovah commissioned them to do.

00:33:00.503 --> 00:33:03.214 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, we want to imitate them.

00:33:03.214 --> 00:33:08.136 line:90% position:50% align:center
We want to trust
that if Jehovah is allowing us to serve,

00:33:08.136 --> 00:33:12.474 line:90% position:50% align:center
even if we might feel very, very inadequate,

00:33:12.474 --> 00:33:15.101 line:90% position:50% align:center
he sees something good in us.

00:33:15.101 --> 00:33:19.397 line:90% position:50% align:center
And he’ll make up for any lack that we feel.

00:33:20.565 --> 00:33:23.568 line:90% position:50% align:center
But here’s a caution:

00:33:23.568 --> 00:33:26.279 line:90% position:50% align:center
Never go to the other extreme.

00:33:26.279 --> 00:33:29.574 line:90% position:50% align:center
Never become overconfident

00:33:29.574 --> 00:33:34.496 line:90% position:50% align:center
and step beyond
the authority that you may be given.

00:33:35.247 --> 00:33:37.875 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, in this regard,
there’s an interesting account

00:33:37.875 --> 00:33:41.754 line:90% position:50% align:center
that I want
to just very briefly share with you.

00:33:41.754 --> 00:33:45.549 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s in 2 Kings chapter 14

00:33:47.551 --> 00:33:49.845 line:90% position:50% align:center
—2 Kings chapter 14.

00:33:51.013 --> 00:33:54.266 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, as you’re turning there,

00:33:54.266 --> 00:33:58.312 line:90% position:50% align:center
in this account,
we read about King Amaziah of Judah.

00:33:58.312 --> 00:34:00.314 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, he had experienced

00:34:00.314 --> 00:34:03.901 line:90% position:50% align:center
a great victory over the Edomites,

00:34:03.901 --> 00:34:08.823 line:90% position:50% align:center
and now
he wanted to go to war against Israel.

00:34:08.823 --> 00:34:13.077 line:90% position:50% align:center
But King Jehoash
sent him a few words of advice.

00:34:14.704 --> 00:34:17.749 line:90% position:50% align:center
And I want you to just read these words,
these few words,

00:34:17.749 --> 00:34:20.043 line:90% position:50% align:center
and especially draw attention
to one sentence.

00:34:20.043 --> 00:34:21.419 line:90% position:50% align:center
So would you read it with me?

00:34:21.419 --> 00:34:24.255 line:90% position:50% align:center
At 2 Kings 14:10,

00:34:25.882 --> 00:34:30.762 line:90% position:50% align:center
he said:
“True, you have struck down Edom,

00:34:30.762 --> 00:34:33.431 line:90% position:50% align:center
so your heart has become arrogant.”

00:34:33.431 --> 00:34:34.432 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, here’s the point.

00:34:34.432 --> 00:34:37.727 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, here’s the sentence
I want you to draw attention to:

00:34:37.727 --> 00:34:41.898 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Enjoy your glory
 but stay in your own house.”

00:34:43.442 --> 00:34:45.193 line:90% position:50% align:center
Isn’t that a great line?

00:34:45.193 --> 00:34:47.571 line:90% position:50% align:center
I’m going to read it one more time.

00:34:47.571 --> 00:34:50.073 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Enjoy your glory,

00:34:50.073 --> 00:34:52.826 line:90% position:50% align:center
“but stay in your own house.

00:34:52.826 --> 00:34:56.413 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Why should you provoke disaster and fall,

00:34:56.413 --> 00:34:58.415 line:90% position:50% align:center
bringing Judah down with you?”

00:34:59.291 --> 00:35:00.709 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, what’s the point?

00:35:00.709 --> 00:35:04.088 line:90% position:50% align:center
You see, Jehoash said to Amaziah:
‘Enjoy the victory.

00:35:04.088 --> 00:35:06.090 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘Yeah, you won a victory.
Enjoy it.

00:35:06.090 --> 00:35:08.092 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘Don’t get a big head.

00:35:08.092 --> 00:35:10.094 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘Don’t push it.

00:35:10.094 --> 00:35:12.304 line:90% position:50% align:center
Stay in your own house.’

00:35:12.304 --> 00:35:14.932 line:90% position:50% align:center
Some Bible translations say “stay at home.”

00:35:16.225 --> 00:35:17.685 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, as it turned out—

00:35:17.685 --> 00:35:21.772 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, you know, you’re Gilead graduates;
you know how it turned out.

00:35:21.772 --> 00:35:25.193 line:90% position:50% align:center
Amaziah did not listen to that advice.

00:35:25.193 --> 00:35:27.737 line:90% position:50% align:center
He went on to fight against Israel,

00:35:27.737 --> 00:35:31.491 line:90% position:50% align:center
and as a result,
he suffered a humiliating defeat.

00:35:32.367 --> 00:35:33.785 line:90% position:50% align:center
What’s the lesson?

00:35:34.827 --> 00:35:39.874 line:90% position:50% align:center
You have had
a wonderful spiritual victory today.

00:35:39.874 --> 00:35:44.879 line:90% position:50% align:center
This is no doubt going to be
one of the happiest days of your entire life

00:35:44.879 --> 00:35:48.300 line:90% position:50% align:center
—graduating from Gilead School.

00:35:48.300 --> 00:35:51.011 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, it’s right
that you should enjoy this day.

00:35:51.011 --> 00:35:53.889 line:90% position:50% align:center
You should find so much pleasure in it

00:35:53.889 --> 00:35:58.226 line:90% position:50% align:center
and feel satisfaction
in what you’ve accomplished.

00:35:58.226 --> 00:36:00.854 line:90% position:50% align:center
But as you experience this joy

00:36:00.854 --> 00:36:03.523 line:90% position:50% align:center
and in the future as you experience the joy

00:36:03.523 --> 00:36:07.236 line:90% position:50% align:center
of taking on new assignments
that will come to you,

00:36:07.236 --> 00:36:09.780 line:90% position:50% align:center
enjoy the moment.

00:36:09.780 --> 00:36:11.824 line:90% position:50% align:center
But stay in your place.

00:36:11.824 --> 00:36:16.036 line:90% position:50% align:center
Never go beyond the limits
of your responsibility

00:36:16.036 --> 00:36:19.081 line:90% position:50% align:center
or the authority that you’ve been given.

00:36:19.081 --> 00:36:22.042 line:90% position:50% align:center
No assignment ever gives us the license

00:36:22.042 --> 00:36:24.712 line:90% position:50% align:center
for us to think that we are somehow superior

00:36:24.712 --> 00:36:27.882 line:90% position:50% align:center
to our brothers or to act in that way.

00:36:27.882 --> 00:36:29.967 line:90% position:50% align:center
See, no doubt one of the qualities

00:36:29.967 --> 00:36:34.889 line:90% position:50% align:center
that Jehovah saw in all of you
is your humility

00:36:34.889 --> 00:36:39.227 line:90% position:50% align:center
—your ability to consider others
as superior to you

00:36:39.227 --> 00:36:42.438 line:90% position:50% align:center
and to treat them in that way.

00:36:42.438 --> 00:36:47.026 line:90% position:50% align:center
Keep that quality,
and even strengthen it.

00:36:47.026 --> 00:36:51.322 line:90% position:50% align:center
You see,
some who disregarded cautions like this

00:36:51.322 --> 00:36:53.533 line:90% position:50% align:center
and who succumbed to pride

00:36:53.533 --> 00:36:57.829 line:90% position:50% align:center
have, like Amaziah,
eventually suffered a painful defeat.

00:36:58.913 --> 00:37:03.919 line:90% position:50% align:center
So, yes,
this has been an especially happy day,

00:37:03.919 --> 00:37:06.880 line:90% position:50% align:center
and you have many reasons to rejoice in it.

00:37:06.880 --> 00:37:10.592 line:90% position:50% align:center
